    <detaileddescription>
<sect1 id="group__core__group_1node_intro">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para>Nodes in AnalysisG represent individual physics objects (particles) within an event graph. Each node can carry multiple features represented as tensors.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__core__group_1node_properties">
<title>Properties</title>
<para>Typical node properties include:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Kinematic variables (pT, eta, phi, energy)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Identification flags</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Quality criteria</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Truth-level information (for training)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__core__group_1node_indexing">
<title>Indexing</title>
<para>Nodes are indexed sequentially within each graph, starting from 0. The node index is used to:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Reference nodes in edge definitions</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Align feature tensors</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Batch multiple graphs together </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
